          "vnum": 2496,
          "name": "Entrance to a Rock-Strewn Cavern",
          "description": "The path climbs steeply as it bends from northwest to east, opening into a brightly lit cavern. Rudimentary stairs have been cut into the stone to ease movement, but streams of water crossing the passageway make the smooth surfaces quite slippery.",
